Task
Random integer from 0 to n
Math.random () returns a random number between 0 (inclusive) and 1 (not inclusive).
Write a function named integerFrom0ToN that takes a positive integer n as an argument and returns a random integer between 0 and n, inclusive.
Examples:
• the integerFrom0ToN (50) function returns any integer from 0 to 50;
• the integerFrom0ToN (30) function returns any integer from 0 to 30;
• integerFrom0ToN (1000) function returns any integer from 0 to 1000.

Solution
function integerFrom0ToN (n) {
 return Math.floor (Math.random () * n + 1);
}
